        "ratings": [
            {
                "comment": "Professor Karu is the goat! I was lucky to have him as my professor of CS252. He is a great instructor with clear explanation of course materials and is very knowledgeable. I wish to take CS552 in the near future",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "He knows his stuff and presents it clearly. Considerate when grading as well",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "I loved this course and Karu is a great instructor! He wrote his own (free!) textbook, and he wrote an application that lets you practice various skills needed for the course (ex. assembly language, tracing state machines). These resources were so helpful. It is clear that Prof. Sankaralingam is committed to teaching and he is plenty qualified.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Karu is a great instructor. He is passionate about the material and really knows what he's talking about. Projects are long and challenging, but grading is very straightforward. Homework is pretty easy and exams are fair. I recommend taking 552 in the spring with the CS department, as those who teach 552 in the ECE department are not that great.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "Karu is a great instructor for this course and has a lot of background knowledge on the topic (he does research with microprocessors). Lectures are easy to understand, but can be a bit boring in the first couple weeks if you already have Verilog experience. Exams are pretty easy, project is long but test scripts used for grading are given to you.",
                "difficulty_rating": 2,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "Karu's a really funny guy, and a really passionate lecturer. Tests were very straightforward (averages around 100% for 3/4 tests). My only qualm with this class was the general inconsistency between the book and lectures/homeworks, although the book we used was brand new so this will probably be better in the future. Textbook simulators were great",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 3
            },
            {
                "comment": "Very excitable teacher. If you pay attention in class you will find success. I skipped class a number of times during the unit on Assembly language, and because of the poor quality of the textbook, there was difficulty in catching up. Textbook is generally decent (was made by a grad student, so it's not legit), but was very lacking for Assembly.",
                "difficulty_rating": 3,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
                "comment": "Took Karu for 252 - he's op. Good class, good teacher, good grader.",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 5
            },
            {
                "comment": "By far the easiest class I took this semester. Professor Karu is a funny and slightly sarcastic guy. Homework is generally straight forward. Overall, I found CS252 to be an enjoyable experience.",
                "difficulty_rating": 1,
                "quality_rating": 4
            },
            {
